{"word":"ἐχθαίρω","slug":"ἐχθαίρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐχθαίρω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔχθος'><el>ἔχθος</el></a>\n<p/><i>to hate, detest</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>ἔχθος ἐχθήρας μέγα</el> <i>hating with</i> great hatred, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be hated, hateful</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a>, <el>ἐχθαρεῖ μὲν ἐξ ἐμοῦ</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}